# Client State Rules

## Split state by purpose

| Kind | Where | Examples |
|------|-------|----------|
| Server state | API + Zustand cache | favorites, groups, preferences |
| UI state | Zustand or local | selected marker, panels, loading |
| Form state | component-local | until submit |

## Optimistic updates

Use only for favorite toggle and group favorite add/remove:

```typescript
// 1. snapshot previous
// 2. apply optimistic change to store
// 3. await API
// 4. on error: restore snapshot + toast
```

## Hooks

- `useUserData` — fetch/mutate favorites and groups via API
- Auth token from `AuthProvider`; attach to every protected request
- Recompute recommendations when places, preferences, or favorites change (memoize input hash)

## Components

- `"use client"` only when needed (hooks, map, interactivity)
- Map markers: batch updates; avoid re-rendering all markers on minor state changes
- Show score breakdown / reasons on recommendation cards
